Rating: 0
Before simmering the soup, use a motor boat hand blender to puree a portion of the soup right in the pot. The starch of the beans will be released and will take on the liquid flavor even more. Simmer slowly to be sure the starch in the whole beans is set and then let it set for an hour. The taste ramps up every minute it sits there. If you CAN, put it in a covered container and refrigerate overnight. NOW you have soup ! !

