Rating: 4
This recipe was a good starting point for experimentation. For first batch, I used dry beans, soaked overnight, instead of canned. Added 1/2 tsp. oregano and juice of 1/4 lime. Had to cook for 3 hours to get beans soft, and needed 4-6 oz. more water. Did not puree, as I like the beans to be whole. Long cooking time dissolved the onions completely and most of the tomatoes as well. Will use fresh diced tomatoes next time, plus 2 bay leaves, and perhaps more oregano and lime juice. When I get spices/proportions right, will try it in a slow cooker. Thanks to Ms. Vaughan, and to all who suggested changes.

