I halved this recipe made this soup in the slow cooker (crock pot). I browned the onions and garlic first, then added them to everything in the cooker. About 2 hours on high, then I pureed part of it, and added 1/2 pound of smoked ham. Another hour on low and it was done. I didn't decrease the cumin or hot sauce though, and thought it came out great! Being in the slow cooker, it was more soupy than stewy as one person reported in a previous review. Added a little fresh lime on top when served, too. Although slow cooking it makes it take longer, I found it easier to not be in front of the stove, especially with a toddler at home!

